Fix UX performance issues, chat loading states, and broken calendar route

Chat:
- Add separate historyLoading flag so thinking dots only appear during AI response, not history fetch
- Show message skeleton while loading conversation history instead of greeting screen
- Add chat/loading.tsx route-level Suspense skeleton for instant navigation feedback

Dashboard shell:
- Remove 300ms opacity fade-in — content visible immediately on load
- Replace 500ms dialog-detection polling with MutationObserver (instant + zero CPU)
- Skip Zustand re-render when worker poll returns unchanged catch-up state

Inbox / People:
- Clear stale data atomically with setLoading(true) to eliminate old-data flash on filter change

Reflections:
- Move CompletionReportPanel inside !loading && !error guard to prevent rendering over skeleton

Calendar:
- Create /calendar/page.tsx with day navigation, event list, empty/error states
  (fixes 404 from the "Full calendar" link on the daily briefing)

Integrations (OAuth popup fix):
- Pre-fetch Nango session token when consent screen opens so nango.auth() fires
  synchronously from the Proceed click, preventing browser popup blocking
- OAuthConsentScreen now shows "Preparing..." while token is loading
- Applied to all three connect flows: settings, onboarding, desktop onboarding

